text: Ante Pavelić may refer to: * Ante Pavelić (1889–1959), leader of Croatian Fascists (Ustaše) and Poglavnik of the Independent State of Croatia (1941-1945) * Ante Pavelić (1869–1938), Croatian and Yugoslav politician, vice-president of the National Council of Slovenes, Croats and Serbs (1918) * Ante Smith Pavelić (1903–1985), Croatian and Yugoslav diplomat and publicist, son of Ante Pavelić (1869–1938)
title: Ante Pavelić (disambiguation)
